ZCZC OE45
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
WEDNESDAY TO SATURDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 152300 UTC
ON WEDNESDAY HIGH PRESSURE IS EXP TO LIE SW OF THE UK WHILST A LARGE LOW
PRESSURE SYSTEM IS CENTRED ACROSS THE NE OF THE NORWEGIAN BASIN. ON THURSDAY
THIS LOW IS EXP TO MOV E TOWARDS NORWAY AS THE HIGH LOCATES NEAR BRITTANY.
ALSO ON THURSDAY A DEVELOPING LOW IS LIKELY TO MOV NE TOWARDS SERN ICELAND.
ON FRIDAY THIS LOW IS EXP TO MOV QCKY EWARDS ACROSS THE FAROES AND INTO
THE NORWEGIAN BASIN WHILST HIGH PRESSURE REMAINS ACROSS SERN ENGLAND. DURING
SATURDAY THE HIGH IS FCST TO RETROGRESS EWARDS AND JOIN WITH ANOTHER ANTICYCLONE
IN THE MID-ATLANTIC. DURING WEDNESDAY NIGHT STRG TO NEAR GALE FORCE WINDS
ARE EXP TO SPREAD EWARDS ACROSS MUCH OF PORTPATRICK. WINDS REMAINING STRG
THURSDAY WITH GALES EXP TO SPREAD INTO THE NW DURING THE EVENING. GALES TRANSFER
EWARDS ON FRIDAY WITH SEV GALES TEMPO POSS IN THE FAR N. WINDS GENERALLY
EASING ON FRIDAY NIGHT BUT REMAINING STRG ACROSS THE NE
